comment: Matthews (DAL) makes incidental contact with Booker (PHO) as he makes contact with the ball.
Booker (PHO) does not step OOB when he regains possession of the ball.
Curry (DAL) exits the lane within 3 seconds.
[Observable in enhanced video] Warren (PHO) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Matthews (DAL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Booker (PHO) that does not affect his SQBR.
Barnes (DAL) makes foot to foot contact with Booker (PHO) that affects his SQBR.
Booker (PHO) takes more than two steps after the gather.
Warren (PHO) makes incidental contact with Barnes (DAL) during rebounding.
Chriss (PHO) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Matthews (DAL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Booker (PHO) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Harris (DAL) firms up his position and sets the screen on Warren (PHO), absorbing the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] RHH shows Barnes (DAL) move his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Warren (PHO) makes contact to Barnes' (DAL) arms that affects his driving shot attempt.
Chriss (PHO) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Matthews (DAL) and Chriss (PHO) briefly engage and separate in the post.
Nowitzki (DAL) sets the screen on Bledsoe (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Nowitzki (DAL) moves his pivot foot.
Chriss (PHO) makes contact with Nowitzki (DAL) that affects his SQBR.
Booker (PHO) legally contests Matthews' (DAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Matthews (DAL) makes body to body contact with Booker (PHO) that affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Booker (PHO) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Matthews (DAL) legally contests Booker's (PHO) shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Booker (PHO) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
